\b \cf0 47. Device Of Blades : moving barricade, goblins
\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\i \cf0 Ahead of you is 10 foot wide corridor that appears to end in a wooden wall with various blades and spikes protruding from it towards out. You immediately realise that the wall is mobile and starting to rush towards you!
\i0 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260
\cf0 The goblins have converted an old cart they captured, boarded up the back end and drove all manner of rusty swords and daggers through the wood. They use this when anyone opens the doors to the main corridor that they don\'92t like. The wooden wall has enough gaps in it for the goblins to easily spot intruders and the carts harnesses have be re-purposed to allow goblins to push it. \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260
\cf0 The cart can only travel as far as the door and is relatively easy to avoid, unless of course the players are being chased into the corridor. However to get passed the adventurers need to hack and move around the wood for a round, making them vulnerable to attacks from the goblins behind.\
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260
\cf0 If the characters face down the cart, they are each attacked at +1 to hit, doing 1d10 damage. It\'92s very difficult to get passed, and takes two combat rounds before a character can engage in hand to hand combat, during which they\'92ll be peppered by arrows. \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280
\cf0 4 Goblin warriors , 2 Goblin archers \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

