\b \cf0 52. Unused sleeping area
\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\i \cf0 You enter into a vacant chamber. It seems to be used as sleeping quarters as many straw pallets occupy the floor. The walls in here are mouldering yellow ochre and faint artwork seems to depict worship of an elder grain goddess. A wooden plaque nailed to the door in the south has goblin-scrawl symbols on it.
\i0 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260
\cf0 Nothing of value will be found by searching, save for a variety of attractively coloured insects. Anyone who can read goblin knows the sign says \'91Hall Of Noshing\'92. Depending on what\'92s going on in the hall beyond, the characters maybe able to hear goblins through the door.\
