\i \cf0 The doors open into a large, smokey chamber. Rough tables and benches are scattered about a smouldering firepit in the centre of the room, and the remains of food and drink are scattered on the floor. A number of goblins are also strewn around the room, some sleeping while sitting at the tables, but most have curled up on floor. The sound of snoring and mumbling spike the smokey gloom. \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\i0 \cf0 There are 1d6 warriors, 1d6 archers, 1d4 stabbers and 3d4 runts sleeping off an banquet here. They\'92ll wake groggily, \uc0\u8722 1 to all rolls in the first 3 rounds of combat if the party attacks. \'a0\'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
Merriment : 
\i Behind the doors you can hear the sounds of many goblins raising their voices in merriment. Bawdy goblin songs, shouting and laughter ring out. \
\
The room beyond is large and smokey, with a fire pit in the centre and numerous low benches and chairs set out chaotically. Steaming cauldrons and dubious flagons of ale throw out strong aromas. Dozens of goblins sit or stand around, some on the tops of benches, singing goblin songs badly. At the far end of the room a goblin sits brooding atop of wooden throne, flanked by heavily armed warriors.  
\i0 \
\
There are 1d6 warriors, 1d6 archers, 1d4 stabbers and 4d4 runts joining in the party, while the goblin king, Grodsnuk and 4 goblin skull cleavers sit at the back.  \
\
Fighting : The sound of crashing and shouting can be heard from behind the door, while occasionally the door thuds slightly as something hits it.\
\
Before you is a scene of utter chaos. A huge goblin brawl is unfolding in the large eating hall before you. Fists and crockery are flying all over the place, while small goblins bite the legs and fingers of their bigger fellows who smash and punch them and each other. Towards the back of the room a large goblin sits wagering with his axe wielding guards on the results of various fights that are going on.  \
\
There are 1d6 warriors, 1d6 archers, 1d4 stabbers and 4d4 runts involved in the mass brawl, while the goblin king, Grodsnuk and 4 goblin skull cleavers sit at the back enjoying the fight.  \
\
King\'92s Court : 
\i From behind the close doors you can make out the unusually deep voice of single goblin, speaking with some confidence. The doors muffle the sound so you can\'92t make out exactly what is being spoken about. \
\
When you open the doors you see a large group of goblins sitting and standing in a huge hall. They all appear to be listening, almost intently, to a large goblin sat on a wooden throne, flanked by axe wielding guards. In front of him stand a vastly fat goblin wearing robes that would suggest he visits a silk merchant often, and a read skinned goblin who seems to have horns. A wild-eyed goblin shaman, dances from foot to foot while the king speaks.\

\i0 \
There are 2d6 warriors, 1d6 archers, 1d4 stabbers and 4d6 runts listen to the latest proclamations, while the goblin king, Grodsnuk and 6 goblin skull cleavers sit at the back with Reaping Madkin, Chamberlin Gutso and Snezak The Horned nearby. If this turns to a fit, it could easily wipe out a low level party of adventurers so use with caution. Most notably Reaping Madkin is here, and will announce the party are the ones from his visions regarding the pig-faced orcs.   \
\
