\b \cf0 54. Goblin living quarters
\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720

\i \cf0 Scattered cots, straw beds, hammocks, blankets, rubbish and small bones litter this room. A number of goblins of various ages and size scatter when you enter and cringe in the corners of the room while a few braver types cluck weapons and eye you expectantly. 
\i0 \
\
This living chamber contains 2d6 runts and 1d4 goblin warriors. It has nothing of value otherwise.\
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\b \cf0 55. Snezak The Horned\'92s room\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\i\b0 \cf0 This chamber is occupied by five goblins, clustered around a table on top of which sits a what might be a map with crudely carved wooden figures on it. Rudely made dice also litter on corner of the table. Four of the goblins quickly clutch their battleaxes and the fifth, a taller, straighter goblin whose slightly red skin and small goat horns make him look quite devilish holds a rapier in one hand while the other arm is bound in well oiled chain mail. At the back of the room are some crude beds. The walls are painted in abstract, repeating patterns which look like they\'92ve been fairly recently added to with spiked skull motifs. 
\i0\b \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\b0 \cf0 \
Somewhere in Snezaks bloodline is something a little devilish, and he has inherited his horns and fire magic from his devilish lineage. He acts as the kings warlord, and is always accompanied by goblin skull cleavers. He has little interest in rule, and is generally given whatever he wants by the king. If the King aligns with the party Snezak will vocally against the plan, and if the party shows any weakness or failure will seek to overthrown the king, kill the PCs and place another king in charge. Snezak definitely wants to be the power behind the throne. \
\
The map shows the two goblin areas, without the secret doors or areas beyond. The wooden pieces look vaguely humanoid, with some coloured red and some green. Hidden beneath Snezak\'92s bed is sack containing 113 g.p. and 5 pieces of platinum. Snezak\'92s rapier is magical and counts as +1 longsword. \
\
Goblin Infernal Strategist, 4 goblin skull cleavers\
\

\b 56. Cooking chamber : Cauldron, chef, magical dagger\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\i\b0 \cf0 The smell of boiled cabbage overpowers all other smells in this cooking chamber. Physically the room is dominated by a huge cauldron that is so large the residence have constructed a stepped platform to reach into it. Currently two goblins stand on this, stirring with a giant copper spoon. Other goblins are rushing around with various foodstuff, all orchestrated by a tall, thin goblin whose apron and oddly tall hat mark him out at the chef. \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\i0 \cf0 The goblins here are unwilling combatants, and have volunteered to work in the dangerous conditions of the kitchen to avoid combat duty. They will defend themselves however. The head chef uses a magical dagger as his chef\'92s knife, and has become quite proficient with it. The two goblin runts on the platform together can use the copper spoon to bash the heads of the adventurers from a position of advantage, attack anyone near at +1 to hit and doing 1d10 damage. They also are protected somewhat and are receive a +1 bonus to their armour class.\
\
The chef will happily engage with anyone who shows the slightest interest in his cooking, and is willing to pay small amounts of money, or provide acceptable rations to anyone who can provide interesting ingredients, with mushrooms, herbs and rabbit being a favourite.\
\
There is enough food that would be edible by the adventurers for months, although much of it will perish over time.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340
\cf0 Chef, Goblin Stabber with a +1 magical dagger\
10 Goblin Runts \
