\b 59. Musterhall and Chamberlain Gutso The Fat\'92s room\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\i\b0 \cf0 This large chamber is unusual in that there ares columns support in the roof. These intricately carved pillars depict cavorting maidens and snakes. A mouldy curtain half bisects the room at the eastern end. 
\i0\b \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\b0 \cf0 Gusto the fat, the kings chamberlain works and often sleeps here. While not unusually clever in other ways he has a head for tallying, counting and remember where things have been left. He\'92ll always have a few goblins around to order about and have run errands. He is cowardly, but his bulk and experience makes him a half-decent fighter, if he has to. Gutso found an iron baton thats has a winged skull head. It\'92s worth 20 g.p. to the right buyer and makes a reasonable club.\
