\b 61. Reaping Madkin\'92s lair\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\i\b0 \cf0 This soot and ink stained chamber is a bizarre mixture of laboratory and artists workroom. Odd alchemical apparatus lies scattered amongst rough wooden easels that hold simplistic but psychedelic paintings, often depicting mushrooms, swirls of colour, stick men and hybrid animals. Numerous dried things hang from hooks, mushrooms, ears, large beetle shells, rotting eyeballs, mice, candle stubs are all in abundance. \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\i0 \cf0 Reaping Madkin, a powerful goblin Hexamancer lairs here. He is a complex character and potentially an ally of the adventurers as detailed in the section on the Grubby Dog tribe. Amongst his belongings is a potion of invisibility and a scroll of protection from energy. He also has a forgotten stash of 7 small sapphires worth 25 g.p. In a wooden box under discarded rubbish. He wears a +1 ring of protection and has a dagger. \
\
