\b 63. Chamber of silence\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\i\b0 \cf0 This strange chamber has been painted black at some point in the past. The goblins have turned it into a storeroom for their junk, and it\'92s full of chipped pots, torn pieces of cloth, broken weapons and empty boxes. 
\i0 \
\
A great enchantment makes this room utterly silent. No noise, however loud can be heard or made in or from it. The goblins find this room too eerie to use, so they turned it into a store room for junk. The goblins therefore haven\'92t found the secret door, which the Star Trap gnomes use to spy on them from time to time. There isn\'92t anything of real worth in here, although there is plenty of wood for fires.\
\
